## New: FRED Client (`fred_client.py`)

Built to replace Alpha Vantage's broken CPI endpoint. Uses the St. Louis Fed FRED API — **truly unlimited, free, no credit card.**

### Available Series
| Key | FRED ID | Description |
|-----|---------|-------------|
| `CPI` | CPIAUCSL | CPI All Urban Consumers |
| `CORE_CPI` | CPILFESL | Core CPI (excl Food & Energy) |
| `PCE` | PCEPI | PCE Price Index |
| `CORE_PCE` | PCEPILFE | Core PCE |
| `UNEMPLOYMENT` | UNRATE | Unemployment Rate |
| `NONFARM` | PAYEMS | Nonfarm Payrolls |
| `GDP` | GDP | Gross Domestic Product |
| `FED_FUNDS` | FEDFUNDS | Federal Funds Rate |
| `SOFR` | SOFR | Secured Overnight Financing Rate |
| `T10Y` | DGS10 | 10-Year Treasury Yield |
| `T2Y` | DGS2 | 2-Year Treasury Yield |
| `SPREAD_10Y2Y` | T10Y2Y | 10Y-2Y Treasury Spread |

### Usage
```python
from live_monitoring.enrichment.apis.fred_client import FREDClient
fc = FREDClient()  # reads FRED_API_KEY from .env

cpi = fc.get_cpi()           # CPI: 326.6 (+0.17% MoM)
unemp = fc.get_unemployment() # Unemployment: 4.4%
spread = fc.get_yield_spread() # 10Y-2Y: 0.59% (not inverted)
snap = fc.get_macro_snapshot() # Full macro dict
text = fc.get_narrative()      # Narrative for agents
```

